In order to bring about the surrender of Alesia and to prevent other forces being added to those in the town, Caesar constructed an elaborate system of fortifications‚ extending fourteen miles. These consisted of deep trenches, high walls, and several rows of sharpened makes, besides others set up at the bottom of pits, which were covered with branches to conceal them.
